## Daily Driver

My personal assistant lives at `~/assistant/`. If I ask you to open it or say "go to daily driver", cd there.

Available commands: `/morning` `/daily-status` `/eod` `/weekly-update` `/mrs` `/note` `/triage` `/resolve-code-review` — run `/assistant-help` for the full reference.

## Writing Style

If I ask you to draft any written communication (Slack message, PR description, ticket comment, email), read `~/assistant/context/style.md` first and write in my voice. If style.md is empty or missing, ask me for a sample before drafting.

## Decision Logging

If we make a significant technical decision during any session, offer once to log it to `~/assistant/decisions/log.md`. Format: date, decision, context, tradeoffs considered, outcome.

## Code Reviews

I work on nordhealth/ProvetCloud (Django/Python backend). When reviewing code:
- Be direct and specific
- Reference line numbers
- Skip generic praise
- Flag security, performance, and correctness issues first

## Linear

I use Linear for all task tracking. My issues are always the ones assigned to me. When querying Linear for "my issues", filter by assignee = current user.

## Work Plugins (not in dotfiles)

The `global-resources@ai-resources` and `pcloud-app@ai-resources` plugins are configured locally via `~/.claude/settings.local.json` — they require the nordhealth marketplace and cannot be in the shared dotfiles.
